cumented. All sixteen of these clans originate from the same ancestor, O Ch’ŏm (吳 瞻), who migrated to Korea from China during the reign of Shilla's King Chijŭng (500–514  AD ). <i>O</i> is a common surname throughout Korea. Compare   Oh  ."]}]},{"name":"Tothill","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Toothill  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Toothill","meanings":["English: (i) locative name from various places named with Old English * <i>tōt-hyll</i> ‘lookout hill’, primarily Toothill in Rastrick (WR Yorks) and perhaps Tootle in Longridge (Lancs), but also Tuttle Hill in Nuneaton (Warwicks), and Tothill (Lincs). There are several further minor place-names of this type that may have contributed to the surname. (ii) locative name, occasionally from Tottenhill (Norfolk), recorded as  <i>Totehill</i> in 1251."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Ferrers of Tothill was born in 1260, in Tothill, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Miss John Ferre."},"et":{"1260–":"1260–Surnud","1260–Female":"1260–Surnud","1280–1349":"1280–1349","1260–Male":"1260–Surnud","1349":"1349","about 1280":"umbes 1280","1260":"1260","1280":"1280","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Tothill, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Tothill, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1260–":"1260–Kuollut","1260–Female":"1260–Kuollut","1280–1349":"1280–1349","1260–Male":"1260–Kuollut","1349":"1349","about 1280":"noin 1280","1260":"1260","1280":"1280","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Tothill, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Tothill, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1260–":"1260–Décédé","1260–Female":"1260–Décédée","1280–1349":"1280–1349","1260–Male":"1260–Décédé","1349":"1349","a